    lesson: 'Price elasticity = |%change in quantity| / |%change in price| = 8/20 = 0.4. Below 1 means inelastic: quantity responds less than price, so a price increase raises total revenue (roughly 1.20 x 0.92 ≈ 1.10, an ~10% rise). The sign of elasticity relative to 1 tells you whether a price move helps revenue.',
    source,
    generated: true,
